HEADWORD: Expilation
<hw>Ex`pi*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>expiatio</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of expilating or stripping off;
plunder; pillage.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This ravenous <qex>expilation</qex> of the state.</q>
